extensionDescription.message: The Startpage Privacy Protection extension provides private search and online data protection.

popupHomeNACallout.message: Privacy Protection is not applicable on this page. We only score regular websites.

popupHomeScoreFourDescription.message: Contains a small number of third-party trackers, and/or one high-risk tracker.

popupHomeScoreOneDescription.message: Contains several trackers, including one or more first-party and high-risk trackers. May not be using HTTPS.

popupHomeScoreThreeDescription.message: Contains third-party trackers, including one or more high-risk trackers.

popupHomeScoreTwoDescription.message: Site may be owned by a major tracking network, or may contain third-party trackers and high-risk trackers.

popupManageTrackersWarning.message: Blocking this domain is known to break websites.

popupReportBreakdownDescription.message: Breakdown of major (owned by a large tracking network) vs. minor trackers that were blocked.

popupReportDisclaimer.message: This data is stored in your browser and cannot be accessed by Startpage.

popupReportScoreDescription.message: Breakdown of privacy scores by percentage of total sites visited.

settingsAllowlistTabAddSiteDescription.message: Once you start adding sites to your Allowed Sites list, they will appear here.

settingsAllowlistTabDescription.message: Startpage Privacy Protection will be turned off on the following sites. This means that the extension will not block anything when you visit the sites listed here, and it will not send the Do Not Track or Global Privacy Control signals.

settingsAllowlistTabSiteWidgetListLabel.message: Widgets you allow on a specific domain will appear on this list.

settingsAllowlistTabWidgetDescription.message: Allow widgets on specific domains. An example of a widget might be a video player like, YouTube, or an audio player, like SoundCloud. Useful on sites where you want this functionality and trust the source.

settingsAllowlistTabWidgetsCallout.message: Once you start allowing specific widgets, they will appear here.

settingsPrivacyTabDNTDescription.message: Send websites the "Global Privacy Control" and "Do Not Track" signals

settingsPrivacyTabHyperlinkDescription.message: Sites use this to track which links you click on, and where these links point to.

settingsPrivacyTabPrefetchDescription.message: Disable your browser from prefetching data it thinks you might use. This may prevent cookies necessary for site functionality.

settingsTrackersTabSearchPlaceholder.message: Search or add a domain to the list

settingsTrackersTabUpdated.message: derived from EFF/Privacy Badger's regularly updated lists.

startpageTagline.message: The world's most private search engine.

tutorialCustomizeDescription.message: In some cases, blocking cookies or domains could interfere with the siteâ€™s ability to fully load. If you trust the source, we give you control to turn off protection, either once or permanently.

tutorialManageDescription.message: By default, the extension will block known trackers and cookies on all sites. However, you will have control whether to allow specific domains or cookies as desired.

tutorialScoreSummaryDescription.message: The privacy report feature contains a breakdown of the privacy scores of the pages you visit, and an overview of the total trackers and cookies.

tutorialScoringDescription.message: To help you understand risk levels, we give each site you visit a privacy score between 1 and 5. Great privacy protections = high privacy score.
